Fig. 26
): DM3 absent; a seta on LA long. Sixth abdominal segment (
Fig. 26
):VM3 present. Seventh abdominal segment (
Fig. 29
): VM3 present; VP1 mostly present or only one side absent. Eighth abdominal segment (
Fig. 26
): DPp1+DPp2 with 2 pores on anterior margin. Ninth abdominal segment (
Figs 34–35
): Dc bearing 7 pairs of setae in posterior half margin; outer setal row on VPc composed of 2 setae and a pore in exterior margin.
